; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0 - - -; "][x_line][/x_column][/x_row][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  style="padding: 0 - - -; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h2" accent="false" class=" custom-header"]Cost of Removing a Tree in Toronto[/x_custom_headline][x_gap size="40px"][x_text class="left-text "]Expect to spend anywhere <strong>between $300 and $3000 for tree removal in Toronto</strong>. The average amount of money you spend on tree removal will depend on many things including the type of tree you want to be removed from your property. Other factors such as the complexity of the job as well as the size and location of the tree will also determine how much you pay.[/x_text][/x_column][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_image type="none" src="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Average-Cost-of-Tree-Removal-in-Toronto.png" alt="Cost of Tree Removal in Toronto" link="false" href="#" title="" target="" info="none" info_place="top" info_trigger="hover" info_content=""][/x_column][/x_row][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h4" accent="false"]Average Cost of Tree Removal In Toronto[/x_custom_headline][x_text]Other than the above add-ons that you may be required to pay, youâ€™ll still have to budget for the actual tree removal process. Itâ€™s too risky to remove a large tree on your property. In fact, <strong>the larger the tree the more expensive</strong> itâ€™s going to be to remove it. For instance, if the tree is really high, the workers may need to climb up before felling it.

If you want to <a href="https://www.almileytree.com"> tree removal </a>of tree fallen on your property, the price may be different from removing a tree that is still intact and healthy. However, the job still requires skill and experience so you have to be extra cautious. Generally, removing a <strong>fallen tree will cost about the same price as a standing tree</strong>. Expect to pay anywhere <strong>between $300 and $3000</strong> for this service.[/x_text][/x_column][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h4" accent="false"]What Type of Tree Needs to Be Removed[/x_custom_headline][x_text]<strong>Not all trees will be given a removal permit in Ontario</strong>. If the tree is in a perfect condition, not located on your private property and is not posing danger to anyone most likely you will not be granted a removal permit. Before receiving a removal permit the tree will be inspected by a professional arborist who will determine following factors:
<ul>
	<li><strong>The tree is dead</strong> and can no longer be saved;</li>
	<li><strong>The tree has it's top broken or it has large damaged limbs</strong> that are a danger to people and property;</li>
	<li><strong>The tree is too close</strong> to the building, power lines or otherÂ structures;</li>
	<li><strong>The tree was damaged</strong> in storm and is now a safety hazard;</li>
	<li><strong>The tree's roots are damaging underground infrastructure</strong> such as water pipes, electrical wires, gas line, etc</li>
	<li><strong>The tree has become a major inconvenience</strong>: it is blocking sunlight, is blocking driveway and/or sidewalk view, is dropping branches, seeds;</li>
</ul>
Please remember while it might look like removing a tree or just a tree branch is easy, it is not advised to make it your DYI project.<strong> In Ontario treeÂ can onlyÂ be safely removed by professional arborist to prevent causing additional problems.</strong> You can avoid serious injuries by hiring expert<strong> <a title="Arborist Toronto" href="https://www.almileytree.com/arborist-toronto/">arborist in Toronto </a></strong> to offer this service.[/x_text][/x_column][/x_row][/x_section][x_section bg_color="#f7f9d2" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 45px 0px 45px 0px; "][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h4" accent="false"]Large Tree Removal Cost: starting from $1500 and up[/x_custom_headline][x_text]Large trees present a greater safety hazard when they need to be removed from oneâ€™s property. This is certainly a removal job you donâ€™t want to attempt by yourself. The <strong>cost of removing a large tree in Toronto is around $1,500 </strong>because of the specialized equipment and high level of skill it takes to get the job done effectively. There are several factors that come to play when determining how much the entire removal job will cost. For instance, if the removal process involves climbing up really high and cutting down the tree in pieces before felling it completely, be prepared to spend more.[/x_text][x_gap size="20px"][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h4" accent="false"]Pine Tree Removal Cost: starting from 500$ and up[/x_custom_headline][x_text]Just like oak trees, pine trees are also quite tall. They have an average height of about 40 feet. Some are up to 60 feet in height. The larger the tree, the more expensive itâ€™s going to be to have it removed. A <strong>small pine tree will cost you approximately $200 to remove whereas a larger one would cost you $1500 or more</strong>. This is because it will require more specialized tools and expert skill to have it removed safely and in an environmentally friendly manner. [/x_text][x_gap size="20px"][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h4" accent="false"]Oak Tree Removal Cost: starting from 500$ and up[/x_custom_headline][x_text]One of the strong tree species known today is Oak. Oak trees are generally tall. The average healthy oak tree has a height of 60 feet. This makes the removal process risky and somewhat complicated. You will pay <strong>between $200 and $1000 to have an oak tree removed in Ontario</strong>.[/x_text][/x_column][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h4" accent="false"]Fallen Tree Removal Cost: starting from $500 and up[/x_custom_headline][x_text]Itâ€™s not uncommon for trees to fall unexpectedly. When this happens, the tree will need to be cleared immediately. Getting rid of a fallen tree is not as complicated as removing a healthy and living tree. However, this type of job has its challenges. Removal must be done carefully using proper equipment to ensure safety and prevent additional damage to the surrounding. Expect to pay <strong>around $75 and $150 to remove a fallen tree</strong> on your property. Youâ€™ll also need to factor in the cost of getting rid of the tree. Whether youâ€™ll choose to have it hauled away or cut up/chipped into pieces, this is likely to come at an extra cost.[/x_text][x_gap size="20px"][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h4" accent="false"]Tree Branch Removal Cost: starting from $300 and up[/x_custom_headline][x_text]There are cases when you only need a tree branch removed. For instance, you may want tree branch removal to prevent obstruction if you notice some of the branches are interfering with the power lines. This is likely to cost you less than having the entire tree removed. Sometimes your utility company can come in and perform the removal process at no extra cost. Small branches are easy to remove using the simple tools you have at home. However, if you donâ€™t consider yourself a handy person, you can hire a professional <strong>to remove tree branches for about $200 to $300 per hour</strong> for this service. If it will take longer to remove lots of branches, expect to pay a lot more.Â [/x_text][/x_column][/x_row][/x_section][x_section parallax="false" bg_image="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Green_back_03.jpg" bg_color="#449322" class="call_to_action" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 45px 0px 45px 0px; "][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/3"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_text class="nomargin" style="margin: 0!important;"]<h4 style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: #ffffff;">Get A Free Quote</span></h4>[/x_text][gravityform id="4" title="false" description="false" ajax="true"][/x_column][x_column bg_color="" type="1/3"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_text class="left-text "]In need of high-quality tree and shrubbery services in the Toronto area? <strong>CALL NOW at <a href="tel:4167493723">416-749-3723 </a></strong> or get in touch with us today to begin benefiting from our fully insured team of experts. We can further inform you on our services, possible solutions to your plant-related problems, and we can even provide a free estimate![/x_text][/x_column][x_column bg_color="" type="1/3"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_gap size="50px"][x_image type="none" src="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/home-2.jpg" alt="Tree Service" link="false" href="#" title="" target="" info="none" info_place="right" info_trigger="hover" info_content="" id="free_label" style="width: 100%; margin: -49px auto 0 auto; min-height: 180px;"][/x_column][/x_row][/x_section][x_section bg_color="#f7f9d2" id="section-services" class="center-text " style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 70px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h2" accent="true" class="man"]Keys to Proper Tree Removal in Toronto[/x_custom_headline][x_gap size="20px"][x_text class="justify-text "]Similar to a <a href="https://crownconstructions.ca/" style="text-decoration: none; color: #3f3f3f;">custom built house</a> trees on your property require custom care. <a href="https://www.almileytree.com/">Tree removal</a> requires careful planning, a high level of skill and proper equipment to get it done effectively. In fact, this is one of those jobs that are potentially dangerous and shouldnâ€™t be left to just anyone. Many factors can push you to remove a tree from your compound. Perhaps the tree is obstructing a beautiful sight in your landscape. You could want it gone because itâ€™s sick, dehydrated or diseased and risks the surrounding plants. Trees that donâ€™t grow well may also need to be removed or become a serious safety hazard in your compound. Whatever your reasons for tree removal Toronto, understand that this is a serious process that needs to be approached with caution.[/x_text][x_gap size="20px"][/x_column][/x_row][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_feature_list animation_offset="50" animation_delay_initial="0" animation_delay_between="170"][x_feature_box title="Always consider the location of the tree" title_color="" text="When removing a tree, one of the most important things to consider is its location. If the tree is away from houses and other obstacles, it will require less effort to remove. However, if the tree is crossing power lines or is very close to your house, there are many risks for damage to occur. In a windy weather trees can down electrical wires which will cause safety hazard and would have to be fixed by licensed electrician (if on private property) or Hydro One. Therefore, we will ensure that all the safety measures are taken for the removal to be done without causing property damage. In fact, trees that are close to obstacles require more complicated techniques and advanced equipment during removal." text_color="" graphic="icon" graphic_size="150px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#095c31" graphic_bg_color="" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="0px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0px" connector_style="solid" connector_color="" graphic_icon="map-marker" graphic_animation="jello" connector_animation="jello"][x_feature_box title="Is your tree damaged?" title_color="" text="After a major storm or high winds, you may notice some damage on your tree. Tree removal needs to be done cautiously in order to prevent additional damage. Remember that damaged trees are riskier to remove because the workers are more likely to be injured. Itâ€™s always worthwhile to have the tree safely removed by an expert. You can avoid serious injuries and a host of other problems." text_color="" graphic="icon" graphic_size="150px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#634f40" graphic_bg_color="" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="0px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0px" connector_style="solid" connector_color="" graphic_icon="unlink" graphic_animation="jello" connector_animation="jello"][x_feature_box title="What affects the cost of tree removal in Toronto?" title_color="" text="The state of the tree will certainly determine the preventative measures that need to be taken during removal. How much you pay for tree removal will depend on many things such as the size, condition, diameter or location of the tree. The longer the tree, the more complicated and risky it is to remove it. A tree that is healthy and strong also requires more effort to remove than a dead, dying or rotting tree. Another important factor that will determine how much you pay for the tree to be removed is its diameter. A thick tree trunk would be harder to remove than a long, slimmer tree." text_color="" graphic="icon" graphic_size="150px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#65ac22" graphic_bg_color="" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="0px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0px" connector_style="solid" connector_color="" graphic_icon="dollar" graphic_animation="jello" connector_animation="jello"][x_feature_box title="Additional services after tree removal in Toronto" title_color="" text="After the tree is removed, you may require additional services such as stump removal, limb chipping, log splitting and hauling away the tree limbs. Make sure you factor this into the total cost of the tree removal service. Sometimes getting rid of a tree is the only way to reduce the potential risks involved when itâ€™s left in your compound. Donâ€™t be quick to handle tree removal on your own. There are so many risks involved and itâ€™s always best to let the pros handle it for you." text_color="" graphic="icon" graphic_size="150px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#879314" graphic_bg_color="" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="0px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0px" connector_style="solid" connector_color="" graphic_icon="leaf" graphic_animation="jello" connector_animation="jello"][/x_feature_list][/x_column][/x_row][/x_section][x_section parallax="false" bg_image="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Green_back_05.jpg" bg_color="#f7f9d2" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 40px 0px 20px 0px; "][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/3"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h3" accent="false" class="center-text "]<block style="color:white">Get A Free Quote</block>[/x_custom_headline][/x_column][x_column bg_color="" type="2/3"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_text][gravityform id=8 title=false description=false ajax=true tabindex=49][/x_text][/x_column][/x_row][/x_section][x_section bg_color="#ffffff" class=" " style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 50px 0px; "][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0 - - -; "][x_line][/x_column][/x_row][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h3" accent="false" class="center-text "]The Tree Removal Process[/x_custom_headline][x_text class="center-text "]A number of activities may need to be carried out during tree removal. Someone may need to climb up the tree and cut it into small and manageable pieces. You may also need to pay an extra fee for hauling away the limbs. Expect to pay an additional cost for the following services.[/x_text][x_gap size="50px"][/x_column][/x_row][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  class="center-text " style="padding: 0 0 0 0; "][x_feature_list animation_offset="20" animation_delay_initial="0" animation_delay_between="300"][x_feature_box title="Limb chipping services" title_color="" text="The tree limbs can be chipped after removal for recycling purposes around the property. Some tree companies have chippers available so they donâ€™t charge much for this service." text_color="" graphic="image" graphic_size="60px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#ffffff" graphic_bg_color="#2ecc71" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="20px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="1px" connector_style="dashed" connector_color="#272727" graphic_image="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/tree_care_01-02.png" graphic_animation="jello" connector_animation="pulse"][x_feature_box title="Estimated cost" title_color="" text="<b>Starting from 200$ and up</b>" text_color="" graphic="image" graphic_size="60px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#ffffff" graphic_bg_color="#ffaa00" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="20px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="1px" connector_style="dashed" connector_color="#272727" graphic_image="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/arborist_report_01-02.png" graphic_animation="jello" connector_animation="pulse"][/x_feature_list][x_feature_list animation_offset="20" animation_delay_initial="0" animation_delay_between="300"][x_feature_box title="Tree trunk removal" title_color="" text="The trunk of the tree needs to be moved elsewhere after the tree is chopped off. Most tree services will offer to cut the tree trunk into smaller sections and even haul them away for you. But expect to pay an extra fee for this." text_color="" graphic="image" graphic_size="60px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#ffffff" graphic_bg_color="#2ecc71" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="20px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="1px" connector_style="dashed" connector_color="#272727" graphic_image="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/tree_removal_01-02.png" graphic_animation="jello" connector_animation="pulse"][x_feature_box title="Estimated cost" title_color="" text="<strong>Starting from 200$ and up</strong>" text_color="" graphic="image" graphic_size="60px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#ffffff" graphic_bg_color="#ffaa00" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="20px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="1px" connector_style="dashed" connector_color="#272727" graphic_image="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/arborist_report_01-02.png" graphic_animation="jello" connector_animation="pulse"][/x_feature_list][x_feature_list animation_offset="20" animation_delay_initial="0" animation_delay_between="300"][x_feature_box title="Stump removal" title_color="" text="The cost of removing the stump is almost always not included. Youâ€™ll often be required to pay extra for this. Stump removal is done using specialized equipment and must be done by a skilled contractor. How much you pay will depend on the diameter of the stump as well as its condition. If the stump is rotten, itâ€™s likely to be cheaper to remove than a healthy stump." text_color="" graphic="image" graphic_size="60px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#ffffff" graphic_bg_color="" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="20px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="1px" connector_style="dashed" connector_color="#272727" graphic_image="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/tree_removal_01-02.png" graphic_animation="jello" connector_animation="pulse"][x_feature_box title="Estimated cost" title_color="" text="<strong>Starting from 300$ and up</strong>" text_color="" graphic="image" graphic_size="60px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#ffffff" graphic_bg_color="#ffaa00" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="20px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="1px" connector_style="dashed" connector_color="#272727" graphic_image="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/arborist_report_01-02.png" graphic_animation="jello" connector_animation="pulse"][/x_feature_list][/x_column][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  style="padding: 0 0 0 0; "][x_image type="none" src="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/How-Much-Should-You-Spend-on-Tree-Removal.jpg" alt="How Much Should You Spend on Tree Removal" link="false" href="#" title="" target="" info="none" info_place="top" info_trigger="hover" info_content=""][x_text class="center-text "][/x_text][/x_column][/x_row][/x_section][x_section parallax="true" bg_pattern="" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_row inner_container="false" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="#ffffff" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][rev_slider featured-section ][/x_column][/x_row][/x_section][x_section bg_color="#ffffff" id="section-whyUs" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 25px 0px; "][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h2" accent="true" class="center-text "]Why Choose Us?[/x_custom_headline][x_gap size="30px"][/x_column][/x_row][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 10px auto 10px auto; padding: 10px 0px 0p20px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  class="left-text " style="padding: 1px 1px 1px 1px; "][x_feature_list][x_feature_box title="Our Advantage" title_color="" text="While some plant problems can be tended to without professional help, there are many cases where hiring an experienced professional  is optimal. There are countless species of trees and plants that need to be dealt with in a variety of ways. 
Our highly trained and knowledgeable team know how to solve your problem in the safest and most effective way possible. 
We will not only cultivate, remove, and refine with the utmost efficiency, but we will also respect your property and the environment in the process. You can also take comfort in the fact that we are 100% certified as well." text_color="" graphic="icon" graphic_size="60px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#ffffff" graphic_bg_color="#fba324" align_h="right" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="20px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="1px" connector_style="dashed" connector_color="#272727" graphic_icon="tree"][x_feature_box title="Flexibility & Versatility" title_color="" text="From maintenance and fertilizing to pruning and removal services, we have an extensive list of tree services to keep your property in pristine shape. We can help you with a particular task or you can even set up a routine maintenance schedule with us to keep your trees and shrubbery sustained when it suits you best. Regular maintenance is ideal for catching problems before they develop into more serious issues. Whether you require short-term or long-term services, we will strive to exceed your expectations with both the quality of our services and the flexibility of our scheduling." text_color="" graphic="icon" graphic_size="60px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#ffffff" graphic_bg_color="#fba324" align_h="right" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="20px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="1px" connector_style="dashed" connector_color="#272727" graphic_icon="wrench"][/x_feature_list][/x_column][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  style="padding: 0px 1px 1px 1px; "][x_feature_list][x_feature_box title="Comprehensive Services" title_color="" text="Need a tree stump removed? We can free up that space for you. Looking to tame those wild shrubs? We can prune those down to give your landscape a more elegant look. Maybe the plant life on your property seems malnourished and needs more attention? 
With our knowledge of plant species and fertilizers we can ensure that those withering trees and shrubs are soon looking their best. We can even provide cabling and bracing services to support and stabilize those trees that are at risk of uprooting. We can start at the beginning and help you plan a new landscape." text_color="" graphic="icon" graphic_size="60px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#ffffff" graphic_bg_color="#fba324" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="20px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="1px" connector_style="dashed" connector_color="#272727" graphic_icon="gears"][x_feature_box title="Experience & Commitment to Care" title_color="" text="At Al Miley & Associates we care about maintaining and enhancing your Toronto propertyâ€™s trees and shrubbery. With fully certified professionals, we provide only the highest quality services to our happy customers all over the Greater Toronto Area. Over the years, we have garnered decades of experience and have proven ourselves adept in both our commercial and residential endeavours. No matter what the job is, we have the knowledge, experience, and versatility to leave your landscape looking stunning." text_color="" graphic="icon" graphic_size="60px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#ffffff" graphic_bg_color="#fba324" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="20px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="1px" connector_style="dashed" connector_color="#272727" graphic_icon="heart"][/x_feature_list][/x_column][/x_row][/x_section][x_section parallax="false" bg_image="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Al-miley-tree-care.jpg" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 45px 0px 45px 0px; "][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h2" accen